    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-16T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-16T02:00:00-05:00" n="49"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d49">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10769: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-16T15:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 16, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 16—6:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. Following from American Consul General at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“March 15, noon. Steamship <hi rend="italic">Chi Ping</hi> of Yangtze
                            Rapid Company with armed naval guard aboard was heavily fired on at
                            mileage 46 to 48 above Ichang yesterday and Lieutenant C. M. Winslow,
                            officer in charge of armed guard, slightly wounded and five Chinese
                            wounded. <hi rend="italic">Chi Ping</hi> was hit about 300 times by
                            rifle bullets and three shells fired at the vessel from field pieces but
                            no hits. Other vessels of Yangtze Rapid Company are being escorted today
                            through the danger zone by the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Tutuila</hi>.
                            Steamship <hi rend="italic">I’Ping</hi> also attacked same place and
                            same day, one Chinese passenger killed. Armed guard returned fire both
                            cases with rifle fire and machine guns, casualties observed among
                            soldiers ashore who directed the fire against the American vessels with
                            rifles, machine guns, and field pieces.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
